Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) for style classification in art, and analyzes the learned representation through correlation analysis (cs.AI). The study also involves a comprehensive analysis of state-of-the-art networks (cs.LG) and the interpretation of the learned representations in relation to art history concepts (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with a large dataset of images (cs.MM) and discusses the quantitative confirmation of art historian observations.
